alcatelIND1IPv6MIB.name: alcatelIND1IPv6MIB

revisions.description: Allow 0 as valid value for alaIPv6InterfaceDADTransmits.
Added neighbour cache limit objects (global, per-VRF, per-interface). Added Local Proxy Neighbor Discovery objects.
Fixed the Notifications to use MIB Module OID.0 as Notifications root.
The latest version of this MIB Module.

alcatelIND1IPv6MIBNotifications.name: alcatelIND1IPv6MIBNotifications
alcatelIND1IPv6MIBNotifications.description: Branch For IPv6 MIB Subsystem Notifications.

AlaIPv6AddressPrefix.name: AlaIPv6AddressPrefix
AlaIPv6AddressPrefix.description: A data type for the 8 byte IPv6 prefixes for EUI-64 addresses

alaIPv6ClearNeighbors.name: alaIPv6ClearNeighbors
alaIPv6ClearNeighbors.description: Clear all non-static entries from the Neighbor table.

alaIPv6PMTUMinLifetime.name: alaIPv6PMTUMinLifetime
alaIPv6PMTUMinLifetime.description: Set the minimum lifetime for entries in the path MTU table.

alaIPv6NeighborStaleLifetime.name: alaIPv6NeighborStaleLifetime
alaIPv6NeighborStaleLifetime.description: Set the minimum lifetime for neighbor entries in the stale state. In older versions of this MIB the default was specified as 1440 minutes.

alaIPv6GlobalID.name: alaIPv6GlobalID
alaIPv6GlobalID.description: The global ID used in the creation of local IPv6 unicast addresses (RFC 4193). An explicit value may be specified for the global ID or this object may be set to all zero to have a global ID be created based on the algorithm from the RFC.

alaIPv6VirtualSourceMAC.name: alaIPv6VirtualSourceMAC
alaIPv6VirtualSourceMAC.description: If set to enable(1) when a packet's source address is a VRRP virtual IPv6 address, the corresponding VRRP virtual MAC will be used as the source L2 address. If set to disable(2), the default, the interface's real MAC will be used as the source L2 address.

alaIPv6NeighborLimit.name: alaIPv6NeighborLimit
alaIPv6NeighborLimit.description: The system-wide maximum size of the neighbor cache. A value of 0 indicates that no limit will be enforced. The minimum value is 200 entries.

alaIPv6NeighborVRFLimit.name: alaIPv6NeighborVRFLimit
alaIPv6NeighborVRFLimit.description: The maximum size of the neighbor cache for a specific VRF. A value of 0 indicates that no limit is set. The minimum value is 200 entries.

alaIPv6InterfaceTable.name: alaIPv6InterfaceTable
alaIPv6InterfaceTable.description: Table allowing the creation and removal of IPv6 interfaces. The table is indexed by ipv6IfIndex. The value of ipv6IfIndex shall be a four byte value in one of the following formats: 0x0000vvvv - The interface for VLAN vvvv 0x0100tttt - The interface for tunnel tttt 0x02000001 - The IPv6 loopback interface The loopback interface configuration cannot be modified.

alaIPv6InterfaceRowStatus.name: alaIPv6InterfaceRowStatus
alaIPv6InterfaceRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of IPv6 interfaces.

alaIPv6InterfaceMtu.name: alaIPv6InterfaceMtu
alaIPv6InterfaceMtu.description: The IPv6 interface's maximum transmission unit.

alaIPv6InterfaceSendRouterAdvertisements.name: alaIPv6InterfaceSendRouterAdvertisements
alaIPv6InterfaceSendRouterAdvertisements.description: Specify whether the router sends periodic router advertisements and responds to router solicitations on the interface. The default value for most interfaces is enable(1). Some interface types (e.g. 6to4 tunnel) cannot send router advertisements so the default (and only) value for those interfaces is disable(2).

alaIPv6InterfaceMaxRtrAdvInterval.name: alaIPv6InterfaceMaxRtrAdvInterval
alaIPv6InterfaceMaxRtrAdvInterval.description: The maximum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast router advertisements from the interface.

alaIPv6InterfaceAdvManagedFlag.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAdvManagedFlag
alaIPv6InterfaceAdvManagedFlag.description: The TRUE/FALSE value to be placed in the 'Managed address configuration' flag field in router advertisements.

alaIPv6InterfaceAdvOtherConfigFlag.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAdvOtherConfigFlag
alaIPv6InterfaceAdvOtherConfigFlag.description: The TRUE/FALSE value to be placed in the 'Other stateful configuration' flag field in router advertisements.

alaIPv6InterfaceAdvReachableTime.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAdvReachableTime
alaIPv6InterfaceAdvReachableTime.description: The value to be placed in the Reachable Time field in the router advertisements sent over this interface. The value zero means unspecified by this router.

alaIPv6InterfaceAdvRetransTimer.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAdvRetransTimer
alaIPv6InterfaceAdvRetransTimer.description: The value to be placed in the Retrans Timer field in the router advertisements sent over this interface. The value zero means unspecified by this router.

alaIPv6InterfaceAdvDefaultLifetime.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAdvDefaultLifetime
alaIPv6InterfaceAdvDefaultLifetime.description: The value to be placed in the Router Lifetime field in the router advertisements sent over this interface. The value MUST be either zero, 1, or between alaIPv6InterfaceMaxRtrAdvInterval and 9000 seconds. The special value zero indicates that the router is not to be used as a default router. The special value 1 indicates that this object's true value should be computed using the formula 3 * alaIPv6InterfaceMaxRtrAdvInterval.

alaIPv6InterfaceName.name: alaIPv6InterfaceName
alaIPv6InterfaceName.description: The mandatory user-assigned name for the interface. Since the loopback interface is created without user interaction, the name 'loopback' will be automatically assigned.

alaIPv6InterfaceAdvSendMtu.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAdvSendMtu
alaIPv6InterfaceAdvSendMtu.description: The TRUE/FALSE value that determines whether the MTU option is sent in Router Advertisements.

alaIPv6InterfaceReachableTime.name: alaIPv6InterfaceReachableTime
alaIPv6InterfaceReachableTime.description: In the absence of any reachability notification, the amount of time a neighbor reached via this interface will remain in the reachable state before transitioning to the stale state. Computed to be between .5 and 1.5 times the alaIPv6InterfaceBaseReachableTime.

alaIPv6InterfaceBaseReachableTime.name: alaIPv6InterfaceBaseReachableTime
alaIPv6InterfaceBaseReachableTime.description: The base value used to compute the reachable time for neighbors reached via this interface. See alaIPv6InterfaceReachableTime above.

alaIPv6InterfaceMinRtrAdvInterval.name: alaIPv6InterfaceMinRtrAdvInterval
alaIPv6InterfaceMinRtrAdvInterval.description: The minimum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast router advertisements from the interface. The time must be a minimum of 3 seconds and no more than .75 times the value of alaIPv6InterfaceMaxRtrAdvInterval. Setting this object to the special value of 0 indicates that the minimum interval should be automatically recalculated using the formula .33 times the value of alaIPv6InterfaceMaxRtrAdvInterval.

alaIPv6InterfaceClockSkew.name: alaIPv6InterfaceClockSkew
alaIPv6InterfaceClockSkew.description: Router Advertisement decrementing timers must be consistent in all Advertisements on the link. The clock skew accounts for link propogation delays and poorly synchronized clocks.

alaIPv6InterfaceRetransTimer.name: alaIPv6InterfaceRetransTimer
alaIPv6InterfaceRetransTimer.description: The amount of time to wait before retransmitting a Neighbor Solicitation during neighbor discovery.

alaIPv6InterfaceDADTransmits.name: alaIPv6InterfaceDADTransmits
alaIPv6InterfaceDADTransmits.description: The number of Neighbor Solicitations to send during Duplicate Address Detection. A value of 0 indicates that DAD will not be performed for addresses assigned to the interface.

alaIPv6InterfaceAdvHopLimit.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAdvHopLimit
alaIPv6InterfaceAdvHopLimit.description: The value placed in the current hop limit field of router advertisements.

alaIPv6InterfaceNeighborLimit.name: alaIPv6InterfaceNeighborLimit
alaIPv6InterfaceNeighborLimit.description: The maximum number o neighbor entries that may be cached on this interface. A value of 0 indicates that no limit is set. The minimum value is 10.

alaIPv6InterfaceRetransBackoff.name: alaIPv6InterfaceRetransBackoff
alaIPv6InterfaceRetransBackoff.description: The neighbor unreachability detection exponential backoff base. A value of 1 indicates the use of fixed interval retransmissions.

alaIPv6InterfaceRetransMax.name: alaIPv6InterfaceRetransMax
alaIPv6InterfaceRetransMax.description: The maximum number of neighbor solicitations to be sent during neighbor discovery or neighbor unreachability detection.

alaIPv6ConfigTunnelTable.name: alaIPv6ConfigTunnelTable
alaIPv6ConfigTunnelTable.description: Table for IPv6 configured tunnels. This table contains the tunnel-specific information extending the corresponding tunnel interface entry in alaIPv6InterfaceTable.

alaIPv6ConfigTunnelEntry.name: alaIPv6ConfigTunnelEntry
alaIPv6ConfigTunnelEntry.description: A entry contains the objects for an IPv6 configured tunnel.

alaIPv6ConfigTunnelV4Source.name: alaIPv6ConfigTunnelV4Source
alaIPv6ConfigTunnelV4Source.description: The source IPv4 address for the tunnel.

alaIPv6ConfigTunnelV4Dest.name: alaIPv6ConfigTunnelV4Dest
alaIPv6ConfigTunnelV4Dest.description: The destination IPv4 address for the tunnel.

alaIPv6InterfaceAddressTable.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAddressTable
alaIPv6InterfaceAddressTable.description: Table allowing the creation and removal of IPv6 addresses assigned to interfaces.

alaIPv6InterfaceAddressEntry.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAddressEntry
alaIPv6InterfaceAddressEntry.description: An IPv6 interface address entry. The same link-local address may be assigned to multiple interfaces. A global address may only be assigned to a single interface.

alaIPv6InterfaceAddressRowStatus.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAddressRowStatus
alaIPv6InterfaceAddressRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of IPv6 interface addresses.

alaIPv6InterfaceAddress.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAddress
alaIPv6InterfaceAddress.description: An IPv6 address (or prefix for EUI-64 addresses) assigned to the interface.

alaIPv6InterfaceAddressPrefixLength.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAddressPrefixLength
alaIPv6InterfaceAddressPrefixLength.description: The number of bits that are significant in the IPv6 address' prefix.

alaIPv6InterfaceAddressAnycastFlag.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAddressAnycastFlag
alaIPv6InterfaceAddressAnycastFlag.description: This object has the value 'true(1)', if this address is an anycast address and the value 'false(2)' otherwise.

alaIPv6InterfaceAddressDADStatus.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAddressDADStatus
alaIPv6InterfaceAddressDADStatus.description: The status of duplicate address detection for this address. The only value that may be set via SNMP is 'check' when the current status is 'duplicate'. In such cases, duplicate address detection will be performed again for the address.

alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressTable.name: alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressTable
alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressTable.description: Table allowing the creation and removal of IPv6 addresses formed by appending an EUI-64 interface identifier to the specified prefix. This table is mainly used for the creation of such addresses. After creation they can be managed via the alaIPv6InterfaceAddressTable.

alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressEntry.name: alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressEntry
alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressEntry.description: An IPv6 interface EUI-64 address entry.

alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressRowStatus.name: alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressRowStatus
alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of IPv6 interface EUI-64 addresses.

alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressPrefix.name: alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressPrefix
alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressPrefix.description: The prefix for the EUI-64 address.

alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressPrefixLength.name: alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressPrefixLength
alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressPrefixLength.description: The number of bits that are significant in the IPv6 address' prefix.

alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressIdentifier.name: alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressIdentifier
alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressIdentifier.description: The interface's EUI-64 identifier which is combined with the prefix to form the IPv6 address.

alaIPv6NeighborTable.name: alaIPv6NeighborTable
alaIPv6NeighborTable.description: The IPv6 neighbor table. Much of this information is available in the RFC-2465 ipv6NetToMediaTable. However, that table does not allow the static configuration of neighbor entries (all objects except for ipv6NetToMediaValid are read-only).

alaIPv6NeighborEntry.name: alaIPv6NeighborEntry
alaIPv6NeighborEntry.description: Each entry contains one IPv6 address to `physical' address equivalence (a neighbor).

alaIPv6NeighborSlot.name: alaIPv6NeighborSlot
alaIPv6NeighborSlot.description: The slot used to reach the neighbor. When creating a static neighbor the slot must be specified. On read, a value of zero indicates the slot is not known/not applicable.

alaIPv6NeighborPort.name: alaIPv6NeighborPort
alaIPv6NeighborPort.description: The port used to reach the neighbor. When creating a static neighbor the port must be specified. On read, a value of zero indicates the port is not known/not applicable.

alaIPv6NeighborType.name: alaIPv6NeighborType
alaIPv6NeighborType.description: The type of the mapping. The 'dynamic(2)' type indicates that the IPv6 address to physical addresses mapping has been dynamically resolved using the IPv6 Neighbor Discovery protocol. The static(3)' types indicates that the mapping has been statically configured. The local(4) indicates that the mapping is provided for an entity's own interface address. All entries added via this table will have the type static(3) and only static entries may be removed via this table.

alaIPv6NeighborState.name: alaIPv6NeighborState
alaIPv6NeighborState.description: The Neighbor Unreachability Detection state for the interface when the address mapping in this entry is used.

alaIPv6NeighborLastUpdated.name: alaIPv6NeighborLastUpdated
alaIPv6NeighborLastUpdated.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this entry was last updated. If this entry was updated prior to the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

alaIPv6NeighborRowStatus.name: alaIPv6NeighborRowStatus
alaIPv6NeighborRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of static entries in the neighbor table.

alaIPv6NeighborLifetime.name: alaIPv6NeighborLifetime
alaIPv6NeighborLifetime.description: The remaining time the neighbor will stay in its current state. External events may cause a state change before the expiry of this lifetime. A value of zero indicates the neighbor will remain in its current state indefinitely.

alaIPv6NeighborReachability.name: alaIPv6NeighborReachability
alaIPv6NeighborReachability.description: The reachability status of the neighbor.

alaIPv6NeighborChassis.name: alaIPv6NeighborChassis
alaIPv6NeighborChassis.description: On a multi-chasis system, the chassis used to reach the neighbor. On a single-chassis system this value is always 0. On read, a value of zero may indicate that the chassis is not known/not applicable.

alaIPv6StaticRouteTable.name: alaIPv6StaticRouteTable
alaIPv6StaticRouteTable.description: This table has been superseded by alaIprmV6StaticRouteTable in ALCATEL-IND1-IPRMV6-MIB. Table allowing the creation and removal of static IPv6 routes.

alaIPv6StaticRouteDest.name: alaIPv6StaticRouteDest
alaIPv6StaticRouteDest.description: The destination IPv6 address of this static route. This object may not take a Multicast address value.

alaIPv6StaticRoutePfxLength.name: alaIPv6StaticRoutePfxLength
alaIPv6StaticRoutePfxLength.description: Indicates the prefix length of the destination address.

alaIPv6StaticRouteIfIndex.name: alaIPv6StaticRouteIfIndex
alaIPv6StaticRouteIfIndex.description: If the next hop address is a link-local address, this is the ipv6IfIndex value of the interface over which the destination is reached. For all other next hop address types the value is zero.

alaIPv6StaticRouteNextHop.name: alaIPv6StaticRouteNextHop
alaIPv6StaticRouteNextHop.description: The IPv6 address of the next hop towards the destination.

alaIPv6StaticRouteMetric.name: alaIPv6StaticRouteMetric
alaIPv6StaticRouteMetric.description: The routing metric for this route. The lower the value, the higher the priority for the static route.

alaIPv6StaticRouteRowStatus.name: alaIPv6StaticRouteRowStatus
alaIPv6StaticRouteRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of static routes.

alaIPv6HostTable.name: alaIPv6HostTable
alaIPv6HostTable.description: Local table mapping host names to IPv6 addresses. This provides the equivalent of /etc/hosts for IPv6.

alaIPv6HostEntry.name: alaIPv6HostEntry
alaIPv6HostEntry.description: A entry maps a host name to an IPv6 address.

alaIPv6HostName.name: alaIPv6HostName
alaIPv6HostName.description: A host name to be mapped to an IPv6 address.

alaIPv6HostAddress.name: alaIPv6HostAddress
alaIPv6HostAddress.description: The IPv6 address mapped to the host name.

alaIPv6HostRowStatus.name: alaIPv6HostRowStatus
alaIPv6HostRowStatus.description: Allows host name/IPv6 address mappings to be created and deleted in this table.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixTable.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixTable
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixTable.description: Table allowing the creation and removal of IPv6 prefixes to be placed in Prefix Information options in Router Advertisement messages sent from the interface. Default: all prefixes that the router advertises via routing protocols as being on-link for the interface from which the advertisement is sent. The link-local prefix is not included in the list of advertised prefixes.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixRowStatus.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixRowStatus
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of IPv6 interface prefixes for Router ADvertisement messages.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefix.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefix
alaIPv6InterfacePrefix.description: The prefix associated with this interface.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixLength.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixLength
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix in bits.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetime.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetime
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetime.description: The value to be placed in the Valid Lifetime in the Prefix Information option, in seconds. The designated value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixOnLinkFlag.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixOnLinkFlag
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixOnLinkFlag.description: The value to be placed in the on-link flag (L-bit) field in the Prefix Information option.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetime.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetime
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetime.description: The value to be placed in the Preferred Lifetime in the Prefix Information option, in seconds. The designated value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixAutonomousFlag.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixAutonomousFlag
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixAutonomousFlag.description: The value to be placed in the Autonomous Flag field in the Prefix Information option.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixSource.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixSource
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixSource.description: The source of this prefix. If configured by management the value will be configured(3). If determined automatically from IPv6 interface address configuration the value will be dynamic(2).

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetimeDecre.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetimeDecrement
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetimeDecre.description: If true, use the remaining seconds derived from alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetime in the Router Advertisement. If false, use the static value alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetime.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetimeExpir.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetimeExpire
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixValidLifetimeExpir.description: The date and time when the advertised prefix Valid Lifetime expires. To use this value, alaIPv6InterfaceValidLifetimeDecrement must be set to true.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetimeD.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetimeDecrement
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetimeD.description: If true, use the remaining seconds derived from alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetime in the Router Advertisement. If false, use the static value alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetime.

alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetimeE.name: alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetimeExpire
alaIPv6InterfacePrefixPreferredLifetimeE.description: The date and time when the advertised prefix Preferred Lifetime expires. To use this value, alaIPv6InterfacePreferredLifetimeDecrement must be set to true.

alaIPv6PMTUTable.name: alaIPv6PMTUTable
alaIPv6PMTUTable.description: Table allowing the retrieval of the known IPv6 path MTU value.

alaIPv6PMTUDest.name: alaIPv6PMTUDest
alaIPv6PMTUDest.description: The destination address of the IPv6 path.

alaIPv6PMTUExpire.name: alaIPv6PMTUExpire
alaIPv6PMTUExpire.description: The minimum time remaining before the PMTU entry is removed from the table.

alaIPv6PMTUHits.name: alaIPv6PMTUHits
alaIPv6PMTUHits.description: The number of times the path MTU entry has been used.

alaIPv6PMTUUpdates.name: alaIPv6PMTUUpdates
alaIPv6PMTUUpdates.description: The number of times the path MTU entry has been updated.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsTable.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsTable
alaIPv6RouteFlagsTable.description: Table allowing the retrieval of the flags for IPv6 route entries.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsUp.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsUp
alaIPv6RouteFlagsUp.description: True if the Up (U) flag is set on the route.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsGateway.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsGateway
alaIPv6RouteFlagsGateway.description: True if the Gateway (G) flag is set on the route.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsHost.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsHost
alaIPv6RouteFlagsHost.description: True if the Host (H) flag is set on the route.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsStatic.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsStatic
alaIPv6RouteFlagsStatic.description: True if the Static (S) flag is set on the route.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsCloneable.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsCloneable
alaIPv6RouteFlagsCloneable.description: True if the Cloneable (C) flag is set on the route.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsDiscard.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsDiscard
alaIPv6RouteFlagsDiscard.description: True if the Discard/Blackhole (B) flag is set on the route.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsECMP.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsECMP
alaIPv6RouteFlagsECMP.description: True if the ECMP (E) flag is set on the route.

alaIPv6RouteFlagsTransient.name: alaIPv6RouteFlagsTransient
alaIPv6RouteFlagsTransient.description: True if route has not been replaced by valid route after takeover.

alaIPv6LocalUnicastTable.name: alaIPv6LocalUnicastTable
alaIPv6LocalUnicastTable.description: Table allowing the creation and removal of local IPv6 unicast addresses (RFC 4193) on an interface.

alaIPv6LocalUnicastEntry.name: alaIPv6LocalUnicastEntry
alaIPv6LocalUnicastEntry.description: An local unicast IPv6 address entry.

alaIPv6LocalUnicastGlobalID.name: alaIPv6LocalUnicastGlobalID
alaIPv6LocalUnicastGlobalID.description: The global ID portion of the local IPv6 unicast address. Leave the value as all zero when adding a new addres to use the alaIPv6GlobalID value.

alaIPv6LocalUnicastSubnetID.name: alaIPv6LocalUnicastSubnetID
alaIPv6LocalUnicastSubnetID.description: The subnet ID portion of the local IPv6 unicast address.

alaIPv6LocalUnicastInterfaceID.name: alaIPv6LocalUnicastInterfaceID
alaIPv6LocalUnicastInterfaceID.description: The interface identifier portion of the local IPv6 unicast address. When alaIPv6LocalUnicastEUI64 is true(1) the value of this object should be all zero.

alaIPv6LocalUnicastPrefixLength.name: alaIPv6LocalUnicastPrefixLength
alaIPv6LocalUnicastPrefixLength.description: The number of bits that are significant in the IPv6 address prefix.

alaIPv6LocalUnicastEUI64.name: alaIPv6LocalUnicastEUI64
alaIPv6LocalUnicastEUI64.description: If true(1) the interface identifier is formed from an automatically generated EUI-64 value.

alaIPv6LocalUnicastRowStatus.name: alaIPv6LocalUnicastRowStatus
alaIPv6LocalUnicastRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of local IPv6 unicast addresses.

alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedTable.name: alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedTable
alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedTable.description: Table allowing the creation and removal of trusted ports for an interface's RA filtering.

alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedEntry.name: alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedEntry
alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedEntry.description: An RA filter trusted port entry.

alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedChassis.name: alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedChassis
alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedChassis.description: On a multi-chasis system, the chassis on which the trusted port resides. On a single-chassis system or when specifying a link aggregation this value is always 0.

alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedSlot.name: alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedSlot
alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedSlot.description: The slot on which the trusted port resides. When specifying a link aggregation this value is always 0.

alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedPort.name: alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedPort
alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedPort.description: The trusted port's physical port number or the id of a link aggregation.

alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedRowStatus.name: alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedRowStatus
alaIPv6RAFilterTrustedRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of an RA filter's trusted ports.

ndpMaxLimitReached.name: ndpMaxLimitReached
ndpMaxLimitReached.description: This notification is generated when hardware table has reached supported Maximum entries. OS6400 will not generate new ARP request for new nexthops

alaIPv6NeighborLimitExceeded.name: alaIPv6NeighborLimitExceeded
alaIPv6NeighborLimitExceeded.description: Notification that the system-wide neighbor cache limit has been exceeded.

alaIPv6NeighborVRFLimitExceeded.name: alaIPv6NeighborVRFLimitExceeded
alaIPv6NeighborVRFLimitExceeded.description: Notification that a per-VRF neighbor cache limit has been exceeded.

alaIPv6InterfaceNeighborLimitExceeded.name: alaIPv6InterfaceNeighborLimitExceeded
alaIPv6InterfaceNeighborLimitExceeded.description: Notification that a per-interface neighbor cache limit has been exceeded.

alaIPv6Compliance.name: alaIPv6Compliance
alaIPv6Compliance.description: The compliance statement for switches with Alcatel IPv6 stack and implementing ALCATEL-IND1-IPV6-MIB.

alaIPv6TunnelConfigGroup.name: alaIPv6TunnelConfigGroup
alaIPv6TunnelConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of Alcatel IPv6 tunneling.

alaIPv6ConfigGroup.name: alaIPv6ConfigGroup
alaIPv6ConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of configuration parameters of Alcatel IPv6 stack.

alaIPv6NeighborGroup.name: alaIPv6NeighborGroup
alaIPv6NeighborGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IPv6 neighbors.

alaIPv6StaticRouteGroup.name: alaIPv6StaticRouteGroup
alaIPv6StaticRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IPv6 static routes.

alaIPv6InterfaceGroup.name: alaIPv6InterfaceGroup
alaIPv6InterfaceGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IPv6 interfaces.

alaIPv6InterfaceAddressGroup.name: alaIPv6InterfaceAddressGroup
alaIPv6InterfaceAddressGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IPv6 addresses assigned to interfaces.

alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressGroup.name: alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressGroup
alaIPv6InterfaceEUI64AddressGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IPv6 EUI-64 addresses assigned to interfaces.
